OL,5,Cnewspaper
OL,7,FThe ASA concluded: "Because the ad had
OL,8,Fthe indirect effect of promoting e-
OL,9,Fcigarettes, which were not licensed as
OL,10,Fmedicines in non-permitted media, we
OL,11,Fconcluded that it breached the Code."
OL,13,FIt ruled that the ad must not appear
OL,14,Fagain.
OL,16,FThe IBVTA said: "A YouGov survey in
OL,17,FJanuary of this year found that less
OL,18,Fthan a quarter of British adults
OL,19,Fsurveyed could correctly identify that
OL,20,Fsmoking is far more harmful than
OL,21,Fvaping.
